{
  "stem": "7739.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And every family had to share their accommodation, and since these people came with nothing, no luggage at all.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So every household was now overcrowded.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Food was getting scarce.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Came the wintertime, you couldn't buy any fuel for the-- for the heating the houses, so it was cold.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Epidemics broke out, although we had doctors-- a couple of Jewish doctors.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had no medicine and people just died needlessly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And as time progressed, it was getting worse and worse.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In our household, we-- we-- we had a mother and two sons from Lodz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had a mother and two daughters and a son from the city of Plotzk.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We gave up our store to a friend of my father's by the name of Lustgarten, he was a tailor, and he was making suits for the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was a man about my stature, and I remember some Gestapo people came there to measure suits-- he had to stand up on a chair, they were so big in relation to him.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he was a master craftsman.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this is-- and they had their favorite shoemakers, and they had their favorite tailors, they had their favorite watch makers.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they held these people high regards, because they were tradesmen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Our house was happened to be in the place where the ghetto was established.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My personal friends were mostly non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We were made to wear-- to wear the armbands, the white armband with the white star of David on it so as to distinguish you between the Jew and the Catholic-- because either there were Jews or there were Catholics, Gentile or Jews.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I hardly wore this-- only when my parents didn't see me.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
